In addition, one of the most important aspects of PCQDs applicability is their sensitivity for Cu2+ detection. Changes in PCQDs solutions FL intensity were tested at different Cu2+ concentrations (1–4 mM) in order to determine the detection range. The resulting data are shown in Fig. 4h. Evidently, a gradual decrease in PL intensity of PCQDs was observed as the Cu2+ concentration in the solution increased, indicating the sensor's sensitive response to varying Cu2+ concentrations. The relation with Cu2+ concentration and FL response is seen in Fig. 4i. The quenching ratio (F0/F) and Cu2+ concentration was shown to have a substantial linear relation (R2=0.9847) with a linear equation in the range of 0–100 M;

                           (3)
                           F0/F=1.034 + 0.035[Cu2+]
